## âœ… Visual Diagram: Terraform Variable Flow

```
Root Module (main.tf, variables.tf, terraform.tfvars)
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Declares root variables (e.g., region, vpc_cidr)
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Assigns values (e.g., via terraform.tfvars)
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ Passes variables to child modules
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ module "vpc" {
â”‚   â”‚      vpc_cidr = var.vpc_cidr
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ }
â”‚
â”œâ”€â”€ module "eks" {
â”‚      subnet_ids = module.vpc.private_subnet_ids
â”‚  }
â”‚
â””â”€â”€ Outputs can also be exposed to CLI or other modules
     
modules/
â”œâ”€â”€ vpc/
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ main.tf          â† builds VPC
â”‚   â”œâ”€â”€ variables.tf     â† declares vpc_cidr, etc.
â”‚   â””â”€â”€ outputs.tf       â† outputs vpc_id, private_subnet_ids
â”‚
â””â”€â”€ eks/
    â”œâ”€â”€ main.tf          â† builds EKS cluster
    â”œâ”€â”€ variables.tf     â† declares cluster_name, subnet_ids
    â””â”€â”€ outputs.tf       â† outputs cluster info (optional)
```

